It's honestly a fantastic album. If you were around at the time it was a major change in direction from what they had been doing and what they were competing against. Ok Computer came out in 1997. A year that also gave us "Mmm Bop", "Tubthumping" and "I Believe I can fly". The Spice Girls were on the top of their game and the music scene was producing some of the most vanilla tunes they could come up with. Natalie Umbriglia's "Torn", The Cardigans "Love Fool". google a list of top songs in the UK during 1997 and it's basically the ultimate 90's playlist, everything you associate with the 90's sound and style... And then Ok Computer came along and songs like Paranoid Android were actually played on the radio and the video was on MTV and it was unlike anything else around it. Maybe it was just the timing of it that makes me have such fond memories of it but I listened to that album for years to come and still do. It was when Radiohead peaked. The Bends was a great album but lacked the dynamic that Ok Computer had. After that, unfortunately (IMO) they went downhill. Kid A was good. Amnesiac not so much...the rest all just blend together as some sort of whale noise experimentation ...but for a brief period in time. Ok Computer opened the minds of a lot of people sick and tired of listening to the most formulaic top 40 shit the industry could muster up.

I share this problem. Recently I've stopped setting 5 alarms as I find this annoys the shit out of me even more. Especially when the snoozes start overlapping and I'm not even falling back to sleep just wait for the next snooze to go off again...dismissing them is a bad idea since I'll just sleep through.
So what I've done to adjust this insane early morning cycle is to set 1 alarm for 1 1/2 before I have to get up and then another Real alarm for 30mins before I need to be up. The first alarm goes off early but it preps me for the next I know is coming in an hour. I don't snooze this one, I dismiss it. I know the real alarm is going off in an hour. I've found this method works. When the first alarm goes off I know I have an hour left in bed and that when the second alarm goes off there is no room for snoozing. Good luck, you are not alone.
